    "what_description": "Haemaria discolor is a species of flowering plant in the family Orchidaceae. It is a terrestrial orchid with a short stem, 2-6 cm in height, and 2-4 ovate-lanceolate leaves, 5-12 cm long, 1.5-3 cm wide, that are arranged on the rhizome. The inflorescence is a raceme, 10-30 cm long, bearing 2-5 flowers, each 2-3 cm in diameter, with a white lip and a greenish-yellow or yellowish-brown column. The flowers have a yellowish-green sepals and petals, with a purple or reddish-purple lip, and a spur 1-2 cm long. It is found in the Himalayas and Southeast Asia, growing in forests and grasslands at elevations of 500-3000 meters.",
