    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Haemaria discolor are flavonoids, alkaloids, saponins, phenolic acids, and glycosides. Flavonoids, particularly kaempferol and quercetin, exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, which contribute to the plant's potential in treating various ailments. Alkaloids, such as berberine and palmatine, display antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory activities, while saponins have been reported to possess anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects. Phenolic acids, including protocatechuic acid and gallic acid, have been shown to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, and glycosides, including isorhapontigenin and kaempferol-3-O-glucoside, have been reported to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. These constituents work synergistically to provide the plant with its medicinal properties, making it a valuable resource for traditional medicine.",
